rows.text: Vacated when Valentine suffered a career-ending injury in a plane crash.
The title becomes the undisputed NWA US Championship in January 1981 after the NWA San Francisco office, the last other promotion to recognize its own United States Champion, closes.
Valentine won via referee stoppage when Piper suffered a large cut over his left ear.

Vacated two weeks following a title defense against Rick Rude which ended in a double pinfall, which aired on May 15, 1993.

Defeated Rude in a rematch. WCW withdraws from the NWA in September 1993; the NWA begins to recognize its own United States Heavyweight champion, but Rhodes remains the recognized champion in WCW. Aired September 11, 1993.
